  "description": "Marty's mother — in 1985, a disillusioned, overweight woman who drinks too much. In 1955, a lively teenager who falls for the boy her father hit with his car — originally George, but now Marty. Her misplaced infatuation with her own future son creates the story's central paradox: Marty must redirect her affection to George or he will never be born.",
